aiResponses.question_61004369: COP 60,000,000 per year (negotiable based on total compensation and benefits)
aiResponses.question_61004375:
Yes. As a Senior Software Engineer at TechCorp (2020–present) and previously at StartupXYZ (2018–2020), I regularly worked shoulder-to-shoulder with customer support and client success teams to resolve customer issues across email, chat, and phone. I took the lead on technical escalations, translating complex technical root causes into clear, empathetic communications for non-technical customers and stakeholders. For example, I coordinated cross-functional incident responses that included direct email follow-ups to affected customers and synchronous calls with enterprise clients to ensure timely resolution and retain trust.

I’ve also built tooling and processes that directly improved customer-facing support. At TechCorp I developed internal diagnostics and dashboards that allowed support agents to identify the most common causes of user-reported errors, reducing the time-to-first-response and enabling support to resolve more queries without engineering intervention. At StartupXYZ I worked on a customer feedback ingestion pipeline that surfaced repeat issues to product and engineering, enabling prioritized fixes and clearer knowledge-base content for support agents.

These experiences gave me hands-on practice in the channels you call out (email, telephone, chat) and taught me how to combine technical troubleshooting with empathy and clear communication. I enjoy mentoring support colleagues on technical topics, creating reproducible steps to diagnose issues, and continuously improving contact-center efficiency through automation and better tooling. I’m excited about the Customer Excellence Analyst role because it combines customer empathy with data-driven process improvement — areas where I have demonstrable impact and enthusiasm.
